    "segments": [
      {
        "lineIndex": 0,
        "text": "[Paik Jong Won Recipe]\nCurious? Just try it out",
        "startMs": 2753,
        "durationMs": 1679,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 1,
        "text": "[Paik Jong Won's Secret Ingredient]",
        "startMs": 4759,
        "durationMs": 1250,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 2,
        "text": "Kimchi Jjigae (kimchi stew) for today",
        "startMs": 6507,
        "durationMs": 1000,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 3,
        "text": "There are many types of kimchi jjigae",
        "startMs": 7820,
        "durationMs": 1876,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 4,
        "text": "I've made various kinds of it",
        "startMs": 9721,
        "durationMs": 2124,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 5,
        "text": "Today, we'll make a quick version",
        "startMs": 11887,
        "durationMs": 3292,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 6,
        "text": "(Kimchi Jjigae Series 1, Quick Ver.)",
        "startMs": 15265,
        "durationMs": 6626,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 7,
        "text": "(pork, rice water,\ncut kimchi, minced garlic)",
        "startMs": 21916,
        "durationMs": 1849,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 8,
        "text": "(spring onions, spicy chili,\nred chili, fine chili powder)",
        "startMs": 23774,
        "durationMs": 2079,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 9,
        "text": "(coarse chili powder, soy sauce,\nsalted shrimp)",
        "startMs": 25878,
        "durationMs": 1670,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 10,
        "text": "Look at the ingredients and\nif you don't have pork shoulder",
        "startMs": 27783,
        "durationMs": 3125,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 11,
        "text": "that's okay",
        "startMs": 30933,
        "durationMs": 2215,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 12,
        "text": "Use any part of pork\nincluding intestines",
        "startMs": 33283,
        "durationMs": 3626,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 13,
        "text": "Even the head meat is okay\nbut they don't usually sell it",
        "startMs": 36979,
        "durationMs": 1959,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 14,
        "text": "Any type of pork is fine",
        "startMs": 38963,
        "durationMs": 1583,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 15,
        "text": "Just cut the meat into pieces",
        "startMs": 40609,
        "durationMs": 2333,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 16,
        "text": "Pork fat is okay, too",
        "startMs": 43043,
        "durationMs": 3209,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 17,
        "text": "When you make kimchi jjigae",
        "startMs": 46281,
        "durationMs": 3125,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 18,
        "text": "you'll start asking for more fat\nwhen buying pork",
        "startMs": 49431,
        "durationMs": 2769,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 19,
        "text": "You have to add the fat\nto bring out the flavor",
        "startMs": 52225,
        "durationMs": 2219,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 20,
        "text": "If you don't like eating fat",
        "startMs": 54469,
        "durationMs": 1460,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 21,
        "text": "just boil the fat in the broth\nand then take it out",
        "startMs": 55954,
        "durationMs": 3000,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 22,
        "text": "Use that broth to cook the stew\nIt's very delicious",
        "startMs": 58979,
        "durationMs": 2321,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 23,
        "text": "Am I revealing too much?",
        "startMs": 61787,
        "durationMs": 1000,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 24,
        "text": "Another tip, saeujeot (salted shrimp)",
        "startMs": 62980,
        "durationMs": 1751,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 25,
        "text": "If you don't have it,\nuse any type of fish sauce at home",
        "startMs": 64862,
        "durationMs": 2918,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 26,
        "text": "Anchovy, sand lance, tuna salted juice",
        "startMs": 67864,
        "durationMs": 3959,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 27,
        "text": "If you don't have salted shrimp",
        "startMs": 71937,
        "durationMs": 1251,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 28,
        "text": "the taste may be slightly different",
        "startMs": 73244,
        "durationMs": 1765,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 29,
        "text": "But use whatever is available",
        "startMs": 75033,
        "durationMs": 2459,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 30,
        "text": "(Cut the spring onions and chili)",
        "startMs": 77703,
        "durationMs": 3750,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 31,
        "text": "They don't have to look as pretty\nas seen here",
        "startMs": 81909,
        "durationMs": 3167,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 32,
        "text": "Just cut them",
        "startMs": 85101,
        "durationMs": 1160,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 33,
        "text": "Big or small, doesn't matter",
        "startMs": 86286,
        "durationMs": 1759,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 34,
        "text": "But never grind them",
        "startMs": 88070,
        "durationMs": 1266,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 35,
        "text": "Mincing is fine",
        "startMs": 89361,
        "durationMs": 2006,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 36,
        "text": "Just cut them however you want",
        "startMs": 91392,
        "durationMs": 1345,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 37,
        "text": "You won't tell the much difference",
        "startMs": 92762,
        "durationMs": 2578,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 38,
        "text": "Don't mind that",
        "startMs": 95365,
        "durationMs": 1426,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 39,
        "text": "Don't try to cut them pretty\nJust try",
        "startMs": 96805,
        "durationMs": 2521,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 40,
        "text": "(Pork 120g)",
        "startMs": 99349,
        "durationMs": 2584,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 41,
        "text": "(Rice water 380ml (2 cups))",
        "startMs": 101958,
        "durationMs": 3381,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 42,
        "text": "One thing, rice water",
        "startMs": 105450,
        "durationMs": 1417,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 43,
        "text": "Rice water is not mandatory",
        "startMs": 107021,
        "durationMs": 1250,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 44,
        "text": "Don't be disappointed if you don't have it",
        "startMs": 108426,
        "durationMs": 1476,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 45,
        "text": "Never be disappointed!",
        "startMs": 109927,
        "durationMs": 3154,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 46,
        "text": "Regular water is fine",
        "startMs": 113155,
        "durationMs": 1653,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 47,
        "text": "Tap water, bottled water",
        "startMs": 114833,
        "durationMs": 2019,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 48,
        "text": "But no soda",
        "startMs": 116877,
        "durationMs": 1000,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 49,
        "text": "No rice water, no problem",
        "startMs": 117993,
        "durationMs": 1488,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 50,
        "text": "I usually use regular water at home",
        "startMs": 119506,
        "durationMs": 1470,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 51,
        "text": "If you use rice water,\nit's a tiny bit more delicious",
        "startMs": 121005,
        "durationMs": 3084,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 52,
        "text": "(Bring to a boil to make\nthe meat broth)",
        "startMs": 125751,
        "durationMs": 2917,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 53,
        "text": "This is the important thing",
        "startMs": 132014,
        "durationMs": 1334,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 54,
        "text": "Put pork in the rice water\nand bring to a boil",
        "startMs": 133373,
        "durationMs": 3502,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 55,
        "text": "Whatever part of pork is fine",
        "startMs": 136981,
        "durationMs": 1417,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 56,
        "text": "Just make sure to boil the pork\nfor a long time",
        "startMs": 138423,
        "durationMs": 3193,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 57,
        "text": "It looks like we're only\nboiling for a while here",
        "startMs": 141695,
        "durationMs": 2583,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 58,
        "text": "But try boiling the broth\nfor a long, long time",
        "startMs": 144303,
        "durationMs": 2466,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 59,
        "text": "You may even forget",
        "startMs": 146794,
        "durationMs": 1772,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 60,
        "text": "that you left something on the stove",
        "startMs": 148591,
        "durationMs": 2417,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 61,
        "text": "You won't be able to chew the meat\nbut the broth will be amazing",
        "startMs": 151026,
        "durationMs": 3709,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 62,
        "text": "Everyone who likes to cook knows this",
        "startMs": 154828,
        "durationMs": 2584,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 63,
        "text": "Using stir-fried pork is better\nwhen making kimchi jjigae",
        "startMs": 157437,
        "durationMs": 2426,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 64,
        "text": "What's the reason?",
        "startMs": 159888,
        "durationMs": 1101,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 65,
        "text": "We melt the fat within the pork",
        "startMs": 161084,
        "durationMs": 2134,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 66,
        "text": "to use that taste to bring out flavor",
        "startMs": 163266,
        "durationMs": 1904,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 67,
        "text": "and let the pork meat be fried\nin its own fat",
        "startMs": 165234,
        "durationMs": 2709,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 68,
        "text": "Then how about boiling?",
        "startMs": 168002,
        "durationMs": 2250,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 69,
        "text": "Bring to a boil",
        "startMs": 170357,
        "durationMs": 1105,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 70,
        "text": "to melt the pork fat into the broth",
        "startMs": 171487,
        "durationMs": 3269,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 71,
        "text": "You'd probably have this experience",
        "startMs": 174781,
        "durationMs": 1363,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 72,
        "text": "You cook pork kimchi jjigae at home",
        "startMs": 176176,
        "durationMs": 4167,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 73,
        "text": "You eat it the next day\nand again the day after",
        "startMs": 180858,
        "durationMs": 2253,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 74,
        "text": "It tastes better as days pass",
        "startMs": 183136,
        "durationMs": 2052,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 75,
        "text": "Do you know why?",
        "startMs": 185213,
        "durationMs": 987,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 76,
        "text": "The more you boil, the more the fat\nmelts from the inside",
        "startMs": 186262,
        "durationMs": 2667,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 77,
        "text": "That's the idea\nSimple, right?",
        "startMs": 188954,
        "durationMs": 1543,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 78,
        "text": "I shouldn't tell you this",
        "startMs": 190522,
        "durationMs": 1167,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 79,
        "text": "(Sliced kimchi 150g)",
        "startMs": 191714,
        "durationMs": 3626,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 80,
        "text": "Kimchi is important here",
        "startMs": 195503,
        "durationMs": 2042,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 81,
        "text": "If you follow my recipe\nbut the kimchi jjigae doesn't taste good",
        "startMs": 197570,
        "durationMs": 2955,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 82,
        "text": "about 50% or 60% of the cases\nare because of kimchi",
        "startMs": 200550,
        "durationMs": 4093,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 83,
        "text": "You need to have good kimchi",
        "startMs": 204663,
        "durationMs": 2703,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 84,
        "text": "Regardless of the taste",
        "startMs": 207391,
        "durationMs": 1926,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 85,
        "text": "what's more important?",
        "startMs": 209342,
        "durationMs": 1364,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 86,
        "text": "You must use fermented kimchi",
        "startMs": 210778,
        "durationMs": 1333,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 87,
        "text": "If you use fresh kimchi,\nthat's just cabbage soup",
        "startMs": 212146,
        "durationMs": 3750,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 88,
        "text": "Never use fresh kimchi",
        "startMs": 215921,
        "durationMs": 1401,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 89,
        "text": "The kimchi must be really sour",
        "startMs": 217425,
        "durationMs": 2709,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 90,
        "text": "Not just regular kimchi",
        "startMs": 220225,
        "durationMs": 2292,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 91,
        "text": "It must be kimchi that tastes\nextremely sour",
        "startMs": 222542,
        "durationMs": 3206,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 92,
        "text": "That sour taste will create a deep\nflavor",
        "startMs": 225809,
        "durationMs": 2107,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 93,
        "text": "Remember this",
        "startMs": 227941,
        "durationMs": 1298,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 94,
        "text": "It must be sour",
        "startMs": 229414,
        "durationMs": 1000,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 95,
        "text": "\"Oh! this is too sour\"\nThat is aged kimchi",
        "startMs": 230534,
        "durationMs": 1626,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 96,
        "text": "We're making kimchi jjigae",
        "startMs": 232229,
        "durationMs": 2230,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 97,
        "text": "So slightly sour",
        "startMs": 234818,
        "durationMs": 751,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 98,
        "text": "(Chopped garlic 30g (2 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 235611,
        "durationMs": 1293,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 99,
        "text": "(Spring onions 30g)",
        "startMs": 236920,
        "durationMs": 1643,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 100,
        "text": "(Hot chili 10g)",
        "startMs": 238588,
        "durationMs": 1440,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 101,
        "text": "(Coarse chili powder 30g (2 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 240053,
        "durationMs": 2556,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 102,
        "text": "(Fine chili powder 30g (2 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 242634,
        "durationMs": 1661,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 103,
        "text": "Many people worry about the chili powder",
        "startMs": 246347,
        "durationMs": 2751,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 104,
        "text": "This person told me once that",
        "startMs": 249130,
        "durationMs": 1384,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 105,
        "text": "she followed my recipe",
        "startMs": 250539,
        "durationMs": 1384,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 106,
        "text": "but the broth got really thick",
        "startMs": 251948,
        "durationMs": 1885,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 107,
        "text": "She used fine chili powder",
        "startMs": 253858,
        "durationMs": 2417,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 108,
        "text": "Fine and coarse powders\nare slightly different",
        "startMs": 256466,
        "durationMs": 2334,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 109,
        "text": "The particles are different",
        "startMs": 258825,
        "durationMs": 2106,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 110,
        "text": "So please, tell the difference\nbetween the two types",
        "startMs": 260956,
        "durationMs": 2918,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 111,
        "text": "But anything's fine, really",
        "startMs": 263899,
        "durationMs": 1722,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 112,
        "text": "Don't follow my recipe from the beginning",
        "startMs": 265741,
        "durationMs": 2876,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 113,
        "text": "Just put 1 tbsp first",
        "startMs": 268642,
        "durationMs": 1324,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 114,
        "text": "because some people don't like spicy food",
        "startMs": 269991,
        "durationMs": 1644,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 115,
        "text": "First find out what you have",
        "startMs": 271660,
        "durationMs": 1885,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 116,
        "text": "whether the chili powder you have\nis spicy or not",
        "startMs": 273570,
        "durationMs": 2679,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 117,
        "text": "and whether it's coarse or fine",
        "startMs": 276274,
        "durationMs": 1312,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 118,
        "text": "I use the fine kind",
        "startMs": 277832,
        "durationMs": 2042,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 119,
        "text": "when I fry dumplings at home",
        "startMs": 279947,
        "durationMs": 2000,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 120,
        "text": "and make dumpling soy sauce",
        "startMs": 282200,
        "durationMs": 1834,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 121,
        "text": "Why am I talking about this?\nStay tuned for our dumpling episode",
        "startMs": 284459,
        "durationMs": 2634,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 122,
        "text": "It's okay if you use just one type\nof chili powder",
        "startMs": 287145,
        "durationMs": 2334,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 123,
        "text": "No problem at all",
        "startMs": 289598,
        "durationMs": 1251,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 124,
        "text": "It just looks a little bit different",
        "startMs": 291033,
        "durationMs": 3709,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 125,
        "text": "Compare later to see",
        "startMs": 294962,
        "durationMs": 1750,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 126,
        "text": "what's different when you use one or two",
        "startMs": 296962,
        "durationMs": 2668,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 127,
        "text": "types of chili powder",
        "startMs": 300091,
        "durationMs": 1417,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 128,
        "text": "Once you start to realize that",
        "startMs": 301561,
        "durationMs": 1829,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 129,
        "text": "you'll have both types in your pantry",
        "startMs": 303424,
        "durationMs": 1675,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 130,
        "text": "(Soy sauce 15ml (1 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 305124,
        "durationMs": 1968,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 131,
        "text": "(Salted shrimp 15g (1tbsp))",
        "startMs": 307099,
        "durationMs": 2125,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 132,
        "text": "Here, guk-ganjang (soy sauce for soup)\nand salted shrimp",
        "startMs": 309495,
        "durationMs": 1834,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 133,
        "text": "Even if you don't have it,\nyou can't use regular soy sauce",
        "startMs": 311499,
        "durationMs": 3417,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 134,
        "text": "Add a little bit of regular soy sauce",
        "startMs": 315023,
        "durationMs": 1668,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 135,
        "text": "Or",
        "startMs": 316919,
        "durationMs": 751,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 136,
        "text": "just use salted juice instead",
        "startMs": 317761,
        "durationMs": 1396,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 137,
        "text": "Or season with salt or salted juice",
        "startMs": 319184,
        "durationMs": 2798,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 138,
        "text": "If you use only regular soy sauce\nits flavor will be overpowering",
        "startMs": 322155,
        "durationMs": 2751,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 139,
        "text": "It probably won't taste like kimchi jjigae",
        "startMs": 325106,
        "durationMs": 2584,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 140,
        "text": "It will taste weird",
        "startMs": 327715,
        "durationMs": 3452,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 141,
        "text": "If you don't have soup soy sauce,",
        "startMs": 331192,
        "durationMs": 1925,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 142,
        "text": "don't go to the grocery store to get one",
        "startMs": 333181,
        "durationMs": 3417,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 143,
        "text": "Don't panic",
        "startMs": 336623,
        "durationMs": 1918,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 144,
        "text": "Just bring out the flavor little\nwith regular soy sauce",
        "startMs": 338566,
        "durationMs": 3611,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 145,
        "text": "and use salt and salted juice",
        "startMs": 342460,
        "durationMs": 1709,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 146,
        "text": "If there's no salted shrimp,\nuse fish sauce",
        "startMs": 344378,
        "durationMs": 2959,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 147,
        "text": "(Add spring onions and chili\nfor garnish, and you're done)",
        "startMs": 347347,
        "durationMs": 3581,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 148,
        "text": "(Kimchi Jjigae Series 1, Quick Ver.)",
        "startMs": 350934,
        "durationMs": 6523,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 149,
        "text": "Try it",
        "startMs": 358409,
        "durationMs": 1000,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 150,
        "text": "(Spring onion 30g)",
        "startMs": 359655,
        "durationMs": 500,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 151,
        "text": "(Spicy chili 10g)",
        "startMs": 360156,
        "durationMs": 526,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 152,
        "text": "(Sliced kimchi 150g)",
        "startMs": 360707,
        "durationMs": 444,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 153,
        "text": "(Pork 120g)",
        "startMs": 361151,
        "durationMs": 519,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 154,
        "text": "(Fine chili powder 30g (2 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 361702,
        "durationMs": 452,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 155,
        "text": "(Chopped garlic 30g (2 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 362154,
        "durationMs": 537,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 156,
        "text": "(Rice water 380ml (1.5 cups))",
        "startMs": 362696,
        "durationMs": 459,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 157,
        "text": "(Soup soy sauce 15g (1 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 363155,
        "durationMs": 500,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 158,
        "text": "(Coarse chili powder 30g (2 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 363655,
        "durationMs": 500,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 159,
        "text": "(Salted shrimp 15g (1 tbsp))",
        "startMs": 364156,
        "durationMs": 542,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 160,
        "text": "(Cut the spring onions and chili)",
        "startMs": 367075,
        "durationMs": 2709,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 161,
        "text": "(Add pork shoulder and water in a pot)\n(Pork 120g, rice water 380ml)",
        "startMs": 370437,
        "durationMs": 3209,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 162,
        "text": "(Bring to a boil to make the meat broth)",
        "startMs": 374032,
        "durationMs": 2875,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 163,
        "text": "(When it's done, add kimchi\nand minced garlic)",
        "startMs": 377181,
        "durationMs": 1054,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 164,
        "text": "(Sliced kimchi 150g, minced garlic 30g)",
        "startMs": 378260,
        "durationMs": 563,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 165,
        "text": "(Add spring onions and chili)\n(Spring onions 30g, spicy chili 10g)",
        "startMs": 378837,
        "durationMs": 2044,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 166,
        "text": "(Add chili powder and mix well)\n(Coarse chili powder 30g, fine chili powder 30g)",
        "startMs": 382317,
        "durationMs": 3004,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 167,
        "text": "(Add soup soy sauce, salted shrimp and stir)\n(Soup soy sauce 15g, salted shrimp 15g)",
        "startMs": 385509,
        "durationMs": 2290,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 168,
        "text": "(Top with spring onions and chili\nas garnish)",
        "startMs": 387846,
        "durationMs": 1471,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 169,
        "text": "[Paik Jong Won's Secret Ingredient]",
        "startMs": 395896,
        "durationMs": 1125,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 170,
        "text": "(Click this)\nFlitto - Finest subtitles translation provider!",
        "startMs": 397046,
        "durationMs": 5041,
        "language": "en"
      },
      {
        "lineIndex": 171,
        "text": "(And this, too)\nFlitto - Finest subtitles translation provider!",
        "startMs": 402110,
